      "code_hash": "0d21b347317a935003c09370ade8b81b",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h1 id=\"nb02-phewas-for-an-rsid\">nb02: PheWAS for an rsID</h1>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Start from an rsID, resolve it to a chr:pos:ref:alt variant, then ask: which traits across\nwhich resources have a credible set that contains this variant? That's a PheWAS view, but\npowered by fine-mapping rather than marginal association \u2014 every dot below is a variant\nsitting inside a 95% credible set, so the signal has already survived LD shrinkage.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Companion to nb01 (gene-first). Same two helpers (<code>fetch_tsv</code>, <code>fetch_json</code>), different\nentry point and a different chart pattern.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "vblA",
      "code_hash": "4e6ca6d0a88e148a27357e419b8441c4",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h3 id=\"entry-point-rs11591147\">Entry point: <code>rs11591147</code></h3>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">PCSK9 R46L \u2014 a missense loss-of-function allele, one of the cleanest natural-experiment variants in cardiometabolic genetics. Carriers have lower LDL cholesterol and lower CHD risk. We expect the PheWAS to light up lipid traits and atherosclerotic disease.</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "bkHC",
      "code_hash": "c81e85570539525f7ea7b48f43da6121",
